cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on developing a Spatial Decomposition Network (SDNet) for factorising 2D medical images into spatial anatomical factors and non-spatial modality factors. This is a computer vision problem, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for semi-supervised segmentation, multi-task segmentation and regression, and image-to-image synthesis, which are all topics that fall under the umbrella of machine learning. Therefore, the paper is also likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper deals with medical images, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a neural network architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
